<p>Robinow syndrome is a genetically heterogeneous disorder characterized by mesomelic limb shortening associated with facial and genital abnormalities (Robinow et al., 1969). Both autosomal dominant and autosomal recessive forms have been described; the recessive form is caused by mutations in the ROR2 gene.</p>

<p>[Robinow, M., Silverman, F. N., Smith, H. D. A newly recognized dwarfing syndrome. Am. J. Dis. Child. 117: 645-651, 1969.]<br/></p>